martial arts advice please i am new to karate i just joined the dojo to help me build up my confidence but i get so scared before each classes and so scared to get hit and make contact i train in the world hardest full contact karate system everyone is very loving and respectful its just me that need to over come all these feeling there are lots of young and pretty girls in the class doing just fine i actually like one girl there but i am so scared and shy and quiet in the dojo i made running away is not an option please advise my heart is already beating fast as i type this i have been so scared to even bring this up to anyone well i started out at a younger age so i wasn't nervous in class but when tests came i was terrified because you had the headmaster watching you and special guests from all around the country and kids families watching you all i thought was that this would end up helping me one day so if i fear it now overcoming that fear later will be harder and it was actually pretty easy all the parents know me now so they are like friends to me another thing is you want to get involved as much as you can so you can get to know the class better and once you are distracted with friends there you will not worry about being scared you will actually forget about it so i hope this worked for you just like it did for me jester by the way do not leave the martial art you are in because that is wjat you chose and should follow and it is a smart choice Martial art Robert Garcia Xiaolin Showdown Ranma __ characters Kodocha Humphrey Bogart Karate EastEnders Kim Possible YuYu Hakusho Shen Gong Wu Jon Secada Charmed Yuri Sakazaki Social rule Judo Kyokushin Sin City Negima Jujutsu Ben Johnson (athlete) One Tree Hill (TV series) Pitaten Double Dragon Mixed martial arts Daredevil Akuma (Street Fighter) Milton H. Erickson The Emancipation of Mimi The Catcher in the Rye Piccolo Junior Saga Shotokan Genseiryu Son Goku (Dragon Ball) AFI 100 Years series Time Out of Mind Saved